                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Conference/4a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 10, 1937—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Supplementing my 45, October 8, 4 p.m. the British Foreign Office has
                    instructed British Chargé d’Affaires at Brussels to approach van Zeeland with
                    the suggestion that latter summon Nine Power Conference to meet in Brussels. You
                    are requested to get in touch with van Zeeland personally and as urgently as
                    possible and convey to him confidentially the expression of the earnest hope of
                    the President and myself that he will accept this suggestion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
